{{Short description|Maldivian politician}} {{Infobox officeholder | name = Abdulla Khaleel | office = Minister Of Health [[Maldives]] | termstart = 17 November 2023 | termend = | president =[[Mohamed Muizzu]] | image =Dr._Abdulla_Khaleel_portrait.jpg }} '''Abdulla Khaleel''' (born 12 February 1975) is a [[Maldivians|Maldivian]] politician who is Minister of Health.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Health |url=https://health.gov.mv/en/executives |access-date=2023-11-18 |website=MinistryOfHealthMV |language=en}}</ref> Khaleel had previously served as Parliament Member for [[Nilandhoo (Faafu Atoll)|Nilandhoo]] Constituency, as well as Secretary General of Civil Service Commission, and Secretary General at PPM. He holds a PhD in Public Policy.<ref>{{Cite web |date=November 17, 2023 |title=Dr. Muizzu’s promising cabinet |url=https://en.sun.mv/85974 |access-date=2023-11-18 |website=SunOnline International |language=en}}</ref>
